data.description: Welcome to a world of opportunity at 110 Hickory Hill Ln, Centerville, GA. This 1.5-story home, built in 1987, is situated on a generous 0.61-acre lot and encompasses 1,839 square feet of living space. It features three bedrooms and two full bathrooms, offering ample space for a growing family or for those seeking extra room for a home office or creative space. The house is an excellent canvas for those looking to infuse their personal style into their next home.  Key aspects of this property include a two-year-old roof ensuring peace of mind against the elements and a solid foundation built on a slab. The interior is ready for a transformative makeover. The exterior, constructed with durable Hardie Board siding, is complemented by a gambrel roof with asphalt shingles, adding character to its facade.  The home's layout presents an open porch and substantial garage space. With its sizable lot, the property offers a blend of spacious outdoor living and privacy, ideal for those who appreciate a sense of openness without sacrificing the convenience of city living.   This property is perfect for investors or homeowners looking for a project to make their own. Situated in a desirable area close to Centerville Elementary School, Thomson Middle School, and Northside High School, it offers a fantastic opportunity to create a dream home in a family-friendly community.  110 Hickory Hill Ln represents not just a house, but a potential-filled home awaiting its next chapter with its new owners.
